<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName LSID="8A17A8A8-9F4C-5C1D-8660-45680D1A8083" authority="Hust. var. atomus in Arch. Hydrobiol. 15: 143, pl. 9, figs 1 - 4. 1938." authorityName="in Arch. Hydrobiol. 15: 143, pl. 9, figs 1 – 4. 1938." class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Stephanodiscaceae" genus="Cyclotella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyclotella atomus subsp. var. var. atomus" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="variety" species="atomus" subSpecies="var." variety="atomus">Cyclotella atomus Hust. var. atomus in Arch. Hydrobiol. 15: 143, pl. 9, figs 1-4. 1938.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Frustule low-cylindrical, central part of the valve is slightly tangentially undulated, 3.6-5.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter, clear boundary between regional and central zones absent, 10-15 striae in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, and a central process (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. SEM (A-F, H) and LM images (G) of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city, valve views: A Stephanodiscus minutulus with arrows shown marginal and central fultoportulae B, C Cyclotella atomus var. atomus with arrows shown marginal and central fultoportulae D-F Cyclotella atomus var. gracilis with arrows shown marginal and central fultoportulae on D picture, only central fultoportula on E and central fultoportula and alveolae on (F) G Cyclotella choctawhatcheeana with arrow shown central fultoportulae H Cyclotella cryptica with arrows shown marginal and central fultoportulae. Scale bars: 3 μm (B, C); 4 μm (D, F); 5 μm (A, E, H); 10 μm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545738" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">6B, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Euplanktonic species, that may exist in marine, brackish or nearshore areas and freshwaters, indicating eutraphentic, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="α-mesosaprobous">α-mesosaprobous</normalizedToken>
conditions and often associated with polluted, warm nutrient-rich water, however particularly tolerating high total phosphorus loads (Denys 1991; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02334251" author="Van Dam, H" journalOrPublisher="Netherlands Journal of Aquatic Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="117 - 133" refId="B128" refString="Van Dam, H, Mertens, A, Sinkeldam, S, 1994. A coded checklist and ecological indicator values of freshwater diatoms from The Netherlands. Netherlands Journal of Aquatic Ecology 28 (1): 117 - 133, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02334251" title="A coded checklist and ecological indicator values of freshwater diatoms from The Netherlands." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02334251" volume="28" year="1994">Van Dam et al. 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-7909.2005.00035.x" author="Yang, X" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Integrative Plant Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="153 - 164" refId="B136" refString="Yang, X, Dong, X, Gao, G, Pan, H, Wu, J, 2005. Relationship between surface sediment diatoms and summer water quality in shallow lakes of the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River. Journal of Integrative Plant Biology 47 (2): 153 - 164, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-7909.2005.00035.x" title="Relationship between surface sediment diatoms and summer water quality in shallow lakes of the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-7909.2005.00035.x" volume="47" year="2005">Yang et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lowe, R" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" publicationUrl="https://diatoms.org/species/cyclotella_atomus" refId="B85" refString="Lowe, R, 2015. Cyclotella atomus. Diatoms of North America. Retrieved March 08, 2020. https://diatoms.org/species/cyclotella_atomus" title="Cyclotella atomus. Diatoms of North America. Retrieved March 08, 2020." url="https://diatoms.org/species/cyclotella_atomus" year="2015">Lowe 2015</bibRefCitation>
), halophilic, alkaliphilic, tolerates higher ion concentrations and frequent osmotic stress as well as high temperature conditions and turbulence (
<bibRefCitation author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B75" refString="Krammer, K, Lange-Bertalot, H, 2000. Bacillariophyceae. Bd. 2., Teil 3: Centrales, Fragilariaceae, Eunotiaceae. Suesswasserflora von Mitteleuropa. Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, Berlin" title="Bacillariophyceae. Bd. 2., Teil 3: Centrales, Fragilariaceae, Eunotiaceae. Suesswasserflora von Mitteleuropa." year="2000">Krammer and Lange-Bertalot 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Valves were found at all investigated sites of the Southern Bug during this research (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
). For Ukrainian territory, it has been reported for the Dnipro River (
<bibRefCitation author="Maystrova, NV" journalOrPublisher="Algologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="467 - 475" refId="B89" refString="Maystrova, NV, Genkal, SI, Scherbak, VI, Semenyuk, NE, 2007. Centrophyceae in the upper section of the Kanev water reservoirs (Ukraine). Algologia 17 (4): 467 - 475" title="Centrophyceae in the upper section of the Kanev water reservoirs (Ukraine)." volume="17" year="2007">Maystrova et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
In general, 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="F.Hustedt" authorityYear="1937" class="Coscinodiscophyceae" family="Stephanodiscaceae" genus="Cyclotella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyclotella atomus" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="atomus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Cyclotella atomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a cosmopolitan species (
<bibRefCitation author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B75" refString="Krammer, K, Lange-Bertalot, H, 2000. Bacillariophyceae. Bd. 2., Teil 3: Centrales, Fragilariaceae, Eunotiaceae. Suesswasserflora von Mitteleuropa. Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, Berlin" title="Bacillariophyceae. Bd. 2., Teil 3: Centrales, Fragilariaceae, Eunotiaceae. Suesswasserflora von Mitteleuropa." year="2000">Krammer and Lange-Bertalot 2000</bibRefCitation>
), widespread in freshwater and marine environments in North America, Europe, and Asia, and has also been recorded from Argentina and South Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Poulickova, A" journalOrPublisher="Nova Hedwigia" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B102" refString="Poulickova, A, 1993. Ecological study of seasonal maxima of centric diatoms. Archiv fuer Hydrobiologie (Supplement 96): 85-106." title="Ecological study of seasonal maxima of centric diatoms. Archiv fuer Hydrobiologie (Supplement 96): 85 - 106." year="1993">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Poulíčková">Poulickova</normalizedToken>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1023965403770" author="Medioli, BE" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Paleolimnology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="353 - 386" refId="B90" refString="Medioli, BE, Brooks, GR, 2003. Diatom and thecamoebian signatures of Red River (Manitoba and North Dakota) floods: Data collected from the 1997 and 1999 spring freshets. Journal of Paleolimnology 29 (3): 353 - 386, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1023965403770" title="Diatom and thecamoebian signatures of Red River (Manitoba and North Dakota) floods: Data collected from the 1997 and 1999 spring freshets." url="https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1023965403770" volume="29" year="2003">Medioli and Brooks 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tanimura, Y" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the National Science Museum Series C" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="5 - 11" refId="B122" refString="Tanimura, Y, Naqumo, T, Kato, M, 2004. A new variety of Cyclotella atomus from Tokyo Bay, Japan: C. atomus var. marina var. nov. Bulletin of the National Science Museum Series C 30: 5 - 11" title="A new variety of Cyclotella atomus from Tokyo Bay, Japan: C. atomus var. marina var. nov." volume="30" year="2004">Tanimura et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-7909.2005.00035.x" author="Yang, X" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Integrative Plant Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="153 - 164" refId="B136" refString="Yang, X, Dong, X, Gao, G, Pan, H, Wu, J, 2005. Relationship between surface sediment diatoms and summer water quality in shallow lakes of the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River. Journal of Integrative Plant Biology 47 (2): 153 - 164, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-7909.2005.00035.x" title="Relationship between surface sediment diatoms and summer water quality in shallow lakes of the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1744-7909.2005.00035.x" volume="47" year="2005">Yang et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wojtal, AZ" journalOrPublisher="Polish Botanical Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="177 - 207" refId="B135" refString="Wojtal, AZ, Kwandrans, J, 2006. Diatoms of the Wyzyna Krakowsko-Czestochowska upland (S. Poland) - Coscinodiscophyceae (Thalassiosirophycidae). Polish Botanical Journal 51 (2): 177 - 207" title="Diatoms of the Wyzyna Krakowsko-Czestochowska upland (S. Poland) - Coscinodiscophyceae (Thalassiosirophycidae)." volume="51" year="2006">Wojtal and Kwandrans 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Filigran, Yaroslavl" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B45" refString="Genkal, SI, Kulikovskiy, MS, Kuznetsova, IV, 2020. Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]. Filigran, Yaroslavl" title="Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]." year="2020">Genkal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
